cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI. 

The paper focuses on entity linking, which is a natural language processing task, and proposes a novel end-to-end neural network model for collective entity linking. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also heavily relies on neural networks and external knowledge, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and semantic interdependence, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
